         <description>"Reynold ""Ray"" Adams, Harold's brother, was born in Golden Meadow, La.,
            around 1944 to Andrew Adams and Letucia Johnfroe Adams. He grew up on Bobs Lane, which
            was home to the Adams and the Collins extended families. Adams's father was a
            refrigeration engineer at an ice plant; Adams also worked there for 13 years after high
            school. In 1976 he became a Golden Meadow deputy police officer, and was eventually
            promoted to chief of police, a position from which he retired. Adams is a practicing
            Catholic. He is married to Judy Adams and has children and four
            grandchildren."</description>
      </name>
